su postgres

psql

CREATE USER documentagent superuser;
ALTER USER documentAgent WITH PASSWORD 'cofits';
ALTER USER postgres WITH PASSWORD 'cofits';

nano /etc/postgres/9.3/main/pg_hba.conf

Replace:
local	all	all			peer
By:
local	all	all			md5

Add at the end:
host	all		all		0.0.0.0/0 	md5

nano /etc/postgresql/9.3/main/postgresql.conf

Replace:
#listen_addresses='localhost'
By:
listen_addresses='*'

/etc/init.d/postgresql restart

Once the server has restarted, try to log in with postgres user:

psql -U postgres (you just set the password to cofits)
If that works try again with documentAgent this time:
psql -U postgres -d postgres (the password is also cofits)